The '''Center for the Neurobiology of Learning and Memory''' ('''CNLM''') is a [[research center]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://catalogue.uci.edu/officeofresearch/ |title=Office of Research < University of California, Irvine – 2013-14 Catalogue |publisher=Catalogue.uci.edu |date= |accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref> established in 1983<ref name="CNLM">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnlm.uci.edu/|title=Center for the Neurobiology of Learning and Memory|website=www.cnlm.uci.edu|access-date=2016-03-10}}</ref> in the [[Francisco J. Ayala School of Biological Sciences]] at the [[University of California, Irvine]] that studies [[memory]] and [[learning]]. Center faculty reported the first known case of [[hyperthymesia]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2011/nov/13/news/la-heb-memory-obsession-brain-20111113 |title=Super memory, obsessive behavior: Do they share brain space? - Los Angeles Times |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=2011-11-13 |accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref> they have also done research on [[false memory syndrome]].<ref>{{cite web|last=George |first=Alison |url=http://www.slate.com/articles/health_and_science/new_scientist/2013/09/elizabeth_loftus_interview_false_memory_research_on_eyewitnesses_child_abuse.html |title=Elizabeth Loftus interview: False-memory research on eyewitnesses, child abuse recovered memories |publisher=Slate.com |date=2013-09-08 |accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref> [[James McGaugh]] was the founding director,<ref name="CNLM"/> and noted memory expert [[Elizabeth Loftus]] is a [[research fellow]] of the center.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[University of California, Irvine]] |url=http://www.cnlm.uci.edu/fellows.htm |accessdate=2012-06-12 |date=n.d. |title=CNLM Fellows at UC Irvine |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120813162923/http://www.cnlm.uci.edu/fellows.htm |archivedate=2012-08-13 |df= }}</ref>
