A '''mycotroph''' is a [[plant]] that gets all or part of its carbon, water, or nutrient supply through [[symbiosis|symbiotic]] association with [[fungus|fungi]]. The term can refer to plants that engage in either of two distinct symbioses with fungi:
*Many mycotrophs have a [[Mutualism (biology)|mutualistic]] association with fungi in any of several forms of '''[[mycorrhiza]]'''. The majority of plant species are mycotrophic in this sense. Examples include [[Burmanniaceae]]. *Some mycotrophs are [[parasitism|parasitic]] upon fungi in an association known as '''[[myco-heterotrophy]]'''.
